My end of studies's project subject mainly concerns the realization of a prototype of intelligent public lighting, aiming to optimize the consumption of electrical energy by ordering the streetlights to light up at 100% of their intensity. lighting only in the event of movement of specific objects by exploiting the techniques of Deep Learning and image recognition to detect and identify these objects circulating on the road during the night, and this of course is accomplished by using a control card, as well as by using the sensors of movements attached to each street lamp and a light sensor so that the system
works only at night.

✅ Materials used:
- Raspberry Pi 3 module B;
- Camera Night vision;
- PIR Infrared Motion Detectors;
- Light sensor;
- Streetlights.

✅ The software environment used:
- Raspberry Pi 32-bit operating system;
- Python programming language;
- The TensorFlow library for the development of a machine learning model;
- The OpenCV library for the image processing part;
- The Numpy library for matrix calculation.
